     1вҶ’# MMS Canvas Knowledge Extraction
     2вҶ’
     3вҶ’## EXT-CANVAS Agent Findings
     4вҶ’**Date:** 2026-01-06
     5вҶ’**Source:** `/apps/canvas/`
     6вҶ’**Purpose:** Extract all knowledge for V2.0 migration
     7вҶ’
     8вҶ’---
     9вҶ’
    10вҶ’## 1. LOD System Implementation
    11вҶ’
    12вҶ’### HYPOTHESIS
    13вҶ’The canvas implements a 3-tier Level of Detail (LOD) system with smooth crossfade transitions between layers.
    14вҶ’
    15вҶ’### EVIDENCE
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’**File:** `apps/canvas/src/canvas/InfiniteCanvas.tsx:70-137`
    18вҶ’
    19вҶ’```typescript
    20вҶ’// LOD Thresholds
    21вҶ’const LOD_THRESHOLDS = {
    22вҶ’  macroToMeso: 0.5,  // Below 0.5 = MACRO
    23вҶ’  mesoToMicro: 2.0,  // Above 2.0 = MICRO
    24вҶ’};
    25вҶ’
    26вҶ’// Size of blend zone around each threshold (+-this value)
    27вҶ’const BLEND_ZONE_SIZE = 0.15;
    28вҶ’
    29вҶ’/**
    30вҶ’ * Calculate layer opacities for smooth LOD transitions
    31вҶ’ */
    32вҶ’function calculateLayerOpacities(zoom: number): {
    33вҶ’  macro: number;
    34вҶ’  meso: number;
    35вҶ’  micro: number;
    36вҶ’} {
    37вҶ’  const { macroToMeso, mesoToMicro } = LOD_THRESHOLDS;
    38вҶ’
    39вҶ’  // Define blend zone boundaries
    40вҶ’  const macroEnd = macroToMeso - BLEND_ZONE_SIZE; // 0.35
    41вҶ’  const mesoStart = macroToMeso + BLEND_ZONE_SIZE; // 0.65
    42вҶ’  const mesoEnd = mesoToMicro - BLEND_ZONE_SIZE; // 1.85
    43вҶ’  const microStart = mesoToMicro + BLEND_ZONE_SIZE; // 2.15
    44вҶ’
    45вҶ’  let macro = 0;
    46вҶ’  let meso = 0;
    47вҶ’  let micro = 0;
    48вҶ’
    49вҶ’  // MACRO opacity: 1 below macroEnd, fade to 0 through blend zone
    50вҶ’  if (zoom <= macroEnd) {
    51вҶ’    macro = 1;
    52вҶ’  } else if (zoom < mesoStart) {
    53вҶ’    const t = (zoom - macroEnd) / (mesoStart - macroEnd);
    54вҶ’    macro = 1 - t;
    55вҶ’  }
    56вҶ’
    57вҶ’  // MESO opacity: fade in, full, fade out
    58вҶ’  if (zoom < macroEnd) {
    59вҶ’    meso = 0;
    60вҶ’  } else if (zoom < mesoStart) {
    61вҶ’    const t = (zoom - macroEnd) / (mesoStart - macroEnd);
    62вҶ’    meso = t;
    63вҶ’  } else if (zoom <= mesoEnd) {
    64вҶ’    meso = 1;
    65вҶ’  } else if (zoom < microStart) {
    66вҶ’    const t = (zoom - mesoEnd) / (microStart - mesoEnd);
    67вҶ’    meso = 1 - t;
    68вҶ’  }
    69вҶ’
    70вҶ’  // MICRO opacity: 0 until mesoEnd, fade in through blend zone
    71вҶ’  if (zoom <= mesoEnd) {
    72вҶ’    micro = 0;
    73вҶ’  } else if (zoom < microStart) {
    74вҶ’    const t = (zoom - mesoEnd) / (microStart - mesoEnd);
    75вҶ’    micro = t;
    76вҶ’  } else {
    77вҶ’    micro = 1;
    78вҶ’  }
    79вҶ’
    80вҶ’  return { macro, meso, micro };
    81вҶ’}
    82вҶ’```
    83вҶ’
    84вҶ’### VERIFICATION: VERIFIED
    85вҶ’- LOD transitions work smoothly in visual testing
    86вҶ’- Both layers render simultaneously during blend zones
    87вҶ’- No "pop-in" effect at layer boundaries
    88вҶ’
    89вҶ’### CRITICAL MIGRATION NOTES
    90вҶ’1. Blend zone size (0.15) must match for smooth UX
    91вҶ’2. Both adjacent layers must render during transitions
    92вҶ’3. Opacity is applied via `transparent={opacity < 1}` on materials
    93вҶ’
    94вҶ’---
    95вҶ’
    96вҶ’## 2. State Management Patterns
    97вҶ’
    98вҶ’### HYPOTHESIS
    99вҶ’The canvas uses `@zazcart/tools` (custom state machine library) instead of React hooks to solve stale closure problems in animation loops.
   100вҶ’
   101вҶ’### EVIDENCE
   102вҶ’
   103вҶ’**File:** `apps/canvas/src/state/canvas-machine.ts`
   104вҶ’
   105вҶ’```typescript
   106вҶ’import { createMachine } from '@zazcart/tools';
   107вҶ’import { viewportSlice } from './viewport';
   108вҶ’import { interactionSlice } from './interaction';
   109вҶ’
   110вҶ’export const canvasMachine = createMachine({
   111вҶ’  id: 'canvas',
   112вҶ’  slices: {
   113вҶ’    viewport: viewportSlice,
   114вҶ’    interaction: interactionSlice,
   115вҶ’  },
   116вҶ’  context: {
   117вҶ’    userID: null,  // Canvas is public/anonymous
   118вҶ’  },
   119вҶ’  // Disable metadata tracking for high-frequency state updates (60fps)
   120вҶ’  metadata: false,
   121вҶ’});
   122вҶ’
   123вҶ’// Typed hooks for React components
   124вҶ’export const useCanvas = canvasMachine.useMachine;
   125вҶ’export const useCanvasSelector = canvasMachine.useSelector;
   126вҶ’
   127вҶ’// Actions for dispatching state changes
   128вҶ’export const canvasActions = canvasMachine.actions;
   129вҶ’
   130вҶ’// Direct store access for animation loops (no React re-render)
   131вҶ’export const canvasStore = {
   132вҶ’  getState: canvasMachine.getState,
   133вҶ’  dispatch: canvasMachine.dispatch,
   134вҶ’  subscribe: canvasMachine.subscribe,
   135вҶ’};
   136вҶ’```
   137вҶ’
   138вҶ’**File:** `apps/canvas/src/state/viewport.ts`
   139вҶ’
   140вҶ’```typescript
   141вҶ’import { createSyncSlice } from '@zazcart/tools';
   142вҶ’
   143вҶ’export interface ViewportSliceState {
   144вҶ’  camera: CameraPosition;
   145вҶ’  canvasSize: CanvasSize;
   146вҶ’  isInitialized: boolean;
   147вҶ’  momentum: MomentumState;
   148вҶ’  animation: AnimationState;
   149вҶ’  isPanning: boolean;
   150вҶ’  panStart: CameraPosition;
   151вҶ’  cameraPosAtPanStart: CameraPosition;
   152вҶ’}
   153вҶ’
   154вҶ’export const viewportSlice = createSyncSlice({
   155вҶ’  id: 'viewport',
   156вҶ’  initial: initialState,
   157вҶ’  cache: { policy: 'session' },
   158вҶ’  reducers: {
   159вҶ’    setCamera(state, payload: CameraPosition) {
   160вҶ’      state.camera = payload;
   161вҶ’    },
   162вҶ’    startMomentum(state, payload: { velocityX: number; velocityY: number }) {
   163вҶ’      state.momentum = {
   164вҶ’        velocityX: payload.velocityX,
   165вҶ’        velocityY: payload.velocityY,
   166вҶ’        isActive: true,
   167вҶ’      };
   168вҶ’    },
   169вҶ’    // ... more reducers
   170вҶ’  },
   171вҶ’});
   172вҶ’```
   173вҶ’
   174вҶ’### USAGE PATTERN IN ANIMATION LOOPS
   175вҶ’
   176вҶ’```typescript
   177вҶ’// In InfiniteCanvas.tsx - Animation loop reads from store directly
   178вҶ’const animate = () => {
   179вҶ’  // Read state from store (always current, no stale closures)
   180вҶ’  const state = canvasStore.getState();
   181вҶ’  const anim = state.viewport.animation;
   182вҶ’
   183вҶ’  if (!anim.isAnimating) {
   184вҶ’    return;
   185вҶ’  }
   186вҶ’
   187вҶ’  const elapsed = Date.now() - anim.startTime;
   188вҶ’  const progress = Math.min(elapsed / anim.duration, 1);
   189вҶ’  const easedProgress = Easing.quadOut(progress);
   190вҶ’
   191вҶ’  // Update via dispatch (not setState)
   192вҶ’  canvasStore.dispatch(
   193вҶ’    canvasActions.viewport.updateAnimation({ camera: clamped })
   194вҶ’  );
   195вҶ’
   196вҶ’  if (progress < 1) {
   197вҶ’    requestAnimationFrame(animate);
   198вҶ’  }
   199вҶ’};
   200вҶ’```
   201вҶ’
   202вҶ’### VERIFICATION: VERIFIED
   203вҶ’- No stale closure issues in momentum/zoom animations
   204вҶ’- State reads are always synchronous via `getState()`
   205вҶ’- Dispatches trigger React re-renders only for subscribed selectors
   206вҶ’
   207вҶ’### CRITICAL MIGRATION NOTES
   208вҶ’1. NEVER use `useState` for animation-related state
   209вҶ’2. Use `canvasStore.getState()` in animation loops, not React hooks
   210вҶ’3. `metadata: false` is critical for 60fps performance (disables object allocations)
   211вҶ’4. Session cache policy means state resets on page refresh
   212вҶ’
