   525вҶ’### 5.2 EntityStore (TypedArray SoA Pattern)
   526вҶ’
   527вҶ’**File:** `apps/canvas/src/entity-store/EntityStore.ts`
   528вҶ’
   529вҶ’```typescript
   530вҶ’/**
   531вҶ’ * Memory layout for N tasks:
   532вҶ’ * - startDay: Float32Array(N) - 4 bytes
   533вҶ’ * - duration: Float32Array(N) - 4 bytes
   534вҶ’ * - trainIndex: Uint16Array(N) - 2 bytes
   535вҶ’ * - type: Uint8Array(N) - 1 byte
   536вҶ’ * - color: Uint8Array(N) - 1 byte
   537вҶ’ * - hasConflict: Uint8Array(N) - 1 byte
   538вҶ’ * - predecessorIndex: Int32Array(N) - 4 bytes
   539вҶ’ * Total: 17 bytes per task = ~1.7MB for 100k tasks
   540вҶ’ */
   541вҶ’
   542вҶ’export interface TaskArrays {
   543вҶ’  startDay: Float32Array;
   544вҶ’  duration: Float32Array;
   545вҶ’  trainIndex: Uint16Array;
   546вҶ’  type: Uint8Array;
   547вҶ’  color: Uint8Array;
   548вҶ’  hasConflict: Uint8Array;
   549вҶ’  predecessorIndex: Int32Array;
   550вҶ’}
   551вҶ’
   552вҶ’class TaskCursorImpl implements TaskCursor {
   553вҶ’  constructor(
   554вҶ’    private readonly store: EntityStore,
   555вҶ’    public readonly index: number
   556вҶ’  ) {}
   557вҶ’
   558вҶ’  get startDay(): number {
   559вҶ’    return this.store.arrays.startDay[this.index];
   560вҶ’  }
   561вҶ’
   562вҶ’  // Computed properties for rendering (zero-allocation)
   563вҶ’  get x(): number {
   564вҶ’    return this.startDay * pxPerDay;
   565вҶ’  }
   566вҶ’
   567вҶ’  get y(): number {
   568вҶ’    return -this.trainIndex * pxPerTrain - pxPerTrain / 2;
   569вҶ’  }
   570вҶ’}
   571вҶ’```
   572вҶ’
   573вҶ’### 5.3 Frustum Culling
   574вҶ’
   575вҶ’**File:** `apps/canvas/src/canvas/layers/MicroLayer.tsx:62-83`
   576вҶ’
   577вҶ’```typescript
   578вҶ’function filterVisibleTasks(tasks: TaskRender[], viewportBounds?: ViewportBounds): TaskRender[] {
   579вҶ’  if (!viewportBounds) return tasks;
   580вҶ’
   581вҶ’  const padding = 100; // Render slightly outside for smooth panning
   582вҶ’  const minX = viewportBounds.minX - padding;
   583вҶ’  const maxX = viewportBounds.maxX + padding;
   584вҶ’  const minY = viewportBounds.minY - padding;
   585вҶ’  const maxY = viewportBounds.maxY + padding;
   586вҶ’
   587вҶ’  return tasks.filter((task) => {
   588вҶ’    const taskStartX = task.startDay * pxPerDay;
   589вҶ’    const taskEndX = taskStartX + task.duration * pxPerDay;
   590вҶ’    const taskY = -task.trainIndex * pxPerTrain - pxPerTrain / 2;
   591вҶ’
   592вҶ’    const xOverlap = taskEndX >= minX && taskStartX <= maxX;
   593вҶ’    const yOverlap = taskY + pxPerTrain / 2 >= minY && taskY - pxPerTrain / 2 <= maxY;
   594вҶ’
   595вҶ’    return xOverlap && yOverlap;
   596вҶ’  });
   597вҶ’}
   598вҶ’```
   599вҶ’
   600вҶ’### VERIFICATION: VERIFIED
   601вҶ’- RBush queries are <0.5ms for 60k items
   602вҶ’- TypedArray storage is ~10x more memory efficient than objects
   603вҶ’- Frustum culling limits HTML labels to visible viewport + padding
   604вҶ’
   605вҶ’### CRITICAL MIGRATION NOTES
   606вҶ’1. Bulk load is faster than individual inserts for RBush
   607вҶ’2. Cursor pattern avoids allocations in hot paths
   608вҶ’3. Always add padding to frustum culling for smooth panning
   609вҶ’4. TypedArray SoA pattern is essential for >50k entities
